(43, 3, 'Special Leave Petition', 'Special Leave Petition', 'special-leave-petition', 'what is Special Leave Petition?', 'Special Leave Petition, Supreme Court', '<h2><strong>what is Special Leave Petition?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>A special leave petition (SLP) is a legal remedy available in some countries, including India, that allows a party to seek permission from a higher court to appeal against a decision of a lower court or tribunal. It is usually filed when there is a significant question of law or a miscarriage of justice involved. An SLP is typically heard and decided by the Supreme Court or the highest court of the respective jurisdiction.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>when is Special Leave petition Filed</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A Special Leave Petition (SLP) is typically filed before the Supreme Court of India to seek special permission to appeal against a judgment or order of a lower court. The timeline for filing an SLP can vary depending on the circumstances of the case. Generally, an SLP should be filed within 90 days from the date of the impugned judgment or order. However, in exceptional cases, the Supreme Court may consider entertaining an SLP even after the expiry of the 90-day period if sufficient reasons are provided. It is always advisable to consult with a legal expert or an advocate to determine the specific timeline and requirements for filing an SLP in a particular case.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '8.png', '', 2),
